detaileddescription.para: Returns the mean value of the last n</n> values observed. Note that if less than n samples values are observed this far, the value returned will only include fewer (i.e. all) samples.

simplesect.para: double : The mean value of the last n</n> values observed so far.

detaileddescription.para: Returns the standard deviation of the last n</n> values observed. Note that if less than n samples values are observed this far, the value returned will only include fewer (i.e. all) samples.

detaileddescription.para: Resets this TallyRunning object by resetting all variables to 0.0 .

Updates this TallyRunning object by fetching the actual value of the ValueSupplier and processing it. The ValueSupplier is passed in the constructor of this TallyRunning object. This update() method complies with the one described in DESMO, see [Page91].

Updates this TallyRunning object with the double value given as parameter. In some cases it might be more convenient to pass the value this TallyRunning will be updated with directly within the update(double val) method instead of going via the ValueSupplier.

parameterdescription.para: double : The value with which this TallyRunning will be updated.

detaileddescription.para: Implementation of the virtual update(Observable, Object) method of the Observer interface. This method will be called automatically from an Observable object within its notifyObservers() method. If no Object (anull value) is passed as arg, the actual value of the ValueSupplier will be fetched with the value() method of the ValueSupplier. Otherwise it is expected that the actual value is passed in the Object arg.

parameterdescription.para: java.util.Observable : The Observable calling this method within its own notifyObservers() method.
Object : The Object with which this TallyRunning is updated. Normally a double number which is added to the statistics or null.

detaileddescription.para: The TallyRunning class is extended from Tally. Same as Tally, it provides statistic analysis about one value (mean, standard deviation, minimum, maximum). In addition, this class is able to calculate this data based on the last n samples only, subject to n passed to the constructor.
